        "trailText":"<p>British Gas joins SSE in raising its prices, as other providers get ready to follow suit in the coming weeks</p>",
        "headline":"Money Talks: British Gas ups the pressure on consumers and Labour leans on payday lenders",
        "body":"<p>Energy price rises keep on coming, with <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/oct/17/british-gas-energy-prices-gas-electricity-centrica\" title=\"\">British Gas the latest to announce a hike</a>. It will raise prices by an average of 9.2% next month, putting further pressure on millions of households battling ever-increasing bills. The average annual dual-fuel bill with British Gas will increase by £107 to £1,297. This follows SSE's 8.2% price hike last week, and other providers are set to follow suit over the coming days and weeks.</p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.guardianenergycomparison.co.uk/guardian_email2\" title=\"\">You can compare and switch energy tariffs using our comparison tool</a></p><p>Payday lending companies will face a crackdown under a Labour government, said Labour leader Ed Miliband. They would be <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2013/oct/17/labour-new-tax-payday-lenders\" title=\"\">hit by higher taxes</a>, with the money raised used to build up their credit union rivals. The levy is intended to raise an additional £13m from the controversial payday loans industry that sees vulnerable borrowers racking up big debts.</p><p>One of the UK's best-known fund managers caused a sensation this week when he announced his intention to move on from his role looking after almost £25bn of clients' money. <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2013/oct/15/neil-woodford-quits-invesco-perpetual\" title=\"Neil Woodford quits Invesco Perpetual in shock departure\">Neil Woodford announced he would leave Invesco Perpetual</a> to set up his own business in April, causing some IFAs to suggest that investors with his funds should also consider a move. Look out for Saturday's Money section of the Guardian where Patrick Collinson will explore the options.</p><p>The housing market was in the news again, as <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2013/oct/15/house-prices-hit-record-high\" title=\"Bank of England signals caution over Help to Buy\">the Office for National Statistics revealed prices had reached a new peak in August</a>, with homes in the UK now costing almost a quarter of a million pounds on average. At the same time, another warning was sounded over the impact of the government's Help to Buy scheme on prices. Some suggest there is already a <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/business/2013/oct/14/britain-housing-bubble-house-prices\" title=\"Is Britain heading for another housing bubble?\">property bubble in London – a subject explored by Jon Henley</a>, who visited some of the capital's hotspots to find out if we are heading for a crash.</p><h2>Also on the site this week</h2><p>• <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2013/oct/15/how-become-arborist-career\" title=\"How do I become  an arborist\">How do I become … an arborist</a>. Anna Tims discovers how to make a living climbing trees</p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/blog/2013/oct/16/equity-release-remortgaging-house\" title=\"Equity release  the gift that keeps on taking\">Equity release – the gift that keeps on taking</a></p><p>• <a href=\"http://www.theguardian.com/money/2013/oct/15/how-sell-royal-mail-shares\" title=\"How do I sell my Royal Mail shares?\">How do I sell my Royal Mail shares?</a> A guide for investors who bought through the government website</p><h2>Daft deal</h2><figure data-media-id='gu-image-420252502'><img src='http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/cartoons/2013/10/17/1382008267659/daft-deal-lidl-chicken-008.jpg' alt='daft deal lidl chicken' width='460' height='276' class='gu-image'/><figcaption>Nul points for Lidl's discounts Photograph: Alastair McDonald</figcaption></figure><p>These chicken pieces aren't really going cheap, despite the big sticker. This fuss about nothing was spotted in Lidl by <a href=\"https://witness.theguardian.com/user/Alastair+McDonald\" title=\"\">Alastair McDonald</a>.</p><p>We would love to hear from you if you have seen similar silly offers. Send your pictures to <a href=\"mailto:money@guardian.co.uk\" title=\"\">money@guardian.co.uk</a> or via <a href=\"https://witness.guardian.co.uk/assignment/51a715bae4b071435a7619ad\" title=\"\">GuardianWitness</a>. The best will be in Saturday's Guardian Money section.</p><h2>Real deals</h2><p>• Last chance to win up to £6,000 towards your mortgage – this competition expires next week. <a href=\"http://guardian.lcplc-online.co.uk/?septcompetition_moneytalksemail\" title=\"\">Find out more here</a>.</p><p>That's all this week.</p><p>Hilary Osborne, editor guardian.co.uk/money</p><p><a href=\"http://www.guardian.co.uk/money/signup/2012/oct/18/1\" title=\"\">Sign up to the Money Talks weekly email for all the latest news and offers</a></p><!-- Guardian Watermark: internal-code/content/420252118|2013-10-17T12:53:00Z|ab5dfab79d61f56a155bc68e3904712a96425312 -->",
